echo =================  TROUBLESHOOTING ===================
echo.
echo Q: When trying to install the software none of the hard disks that I select
echo    Is accepted by the installation program. What's wrong?
echo A: Try to free some more space on your hard disk. Probably you have no enough
echo    free space for the installation.
echo.
echo Q: Why when I run the game I got just the "Loading..." message and crash?
echo A: Be sure that you are on the MOON directory before run the game.
echo    Another cause can be the you have aborted the sound card configuration.
echo    The program REQUIRES a sound driver, even if this driver is the "No digital
echo    sound card" or "PC Speaker" options. If you really don't want any kind of
echo    noise go to the game menu "Options" and disable the Effects and Music.
echo.
echo Q: What means when I try to run the game and the following message appears:
echo    "FATAL ERROR: Impossible to allocate memory ......."?
echo A: You need to free some more base memory for the game. A easy way to do that
echo    is press F5 during the DOS initialization, after you have turned the
echo    computer on, in order to skip the CONFIG.SYS and the AUTOEXEC.BAT.
echo    If it doesn't solve the problem press F8 instead and answer yes just to
echo    the commands HIMEM.SYS and DOS=HIGH (or DOS=HIGH,UMB).
echo.
