echo Q: Everything is fine but the music, that is too much higher or lower than the
echo    sound effects. What to do to solve this?
echo A: Use the proper DOS utility that is provided with your sound card to adjust
echo    the music and the digital sound volume and set it to better levels. Each
echo    board have their own program and can be called MIXER, MIXSET, SETSOUND, etc.
echo.
echo Q: Can I use my joystick with this game?
echo A: No. This game was designed to be played using the keyboard.
echo.
echo Q: Why I got a "File corrupt" message even if I have installed all the files
echo    successfully? Sometimes it runs but later it crashes with "STACK OVERFLOW".
echo A: If you really installed it correctly the problem may be that you are
echo    running on the limit of the necessary memory and there is no space for
echo    the game internal file handlers.
echo.
echo Q: Some sounds seems to be clipped. For example: When it's supposed to be 
echo    heard "Ok. Ready to return" it sounds "Ok. Ready to ret" instead. Why?
echo A: You probably are running with the minimum of the necessary memory, so
echo    the program "cut" some sounds to free some more memory.
echo.
